  {
    "id": 15,
    "documentId": "oo405s0jxa8g3p2ah9ngwd6e",
    "title": "Beyond Dark Mode: Building a 3-Theme System with CSS Variables and JavaScript",
    "slug": "beyond-dark-mode",
    "publishedDate": "2026-06-20",
    "createdAt": "2026-06-20T04:40:30.361Z",
    "updatedAt": "2026-06-29T06:58:24.300Z",
    "publishedAt": "2026-06-29T06:58:24.348Z",
    "excerpt": "Learn how to implement light, dark, and custom brand themes using modern CSS, a segmented toggle switch UI, and a few lines of JavaScript.",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🌗 Introduction",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Dark mode has become standard across modern interfaces. But users today expect more than just light and dark — they expect choice and personalization.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "In this tutorial, we’ll build a scalable 3-theme system with:",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "☀️ Light theme",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🌙 Dark theme",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🎨 Brand theme",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "And instead of basic buttons, we’ll use a modern segmented toggle switch UI that feels polished and intuitive.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🧠 Step 1: Define your design tokens",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Start by defining reusable CSS variables for your UI:",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Apply them throughout your layout:",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🌙 Step 2: Add your theme variants",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Use a data-theme attribute on the <html> element to switch themes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Dark theme",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Now your UI can switch between three visual styles instantly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🎚️ Step 3: Build a modern segmented toggle switch",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Instead of separate buttons, we’ll build a sliding toggle control.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "This creates a smooth animated toggle that slides between the three options.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "⚙️ Step 4: Add JavaScript to power the toggle",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Now we connect the UI to your theme system.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "HTML",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "💾 Step 5: Persist user preference",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Using localStorage, your site now:",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "remembers the selected theme",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "restores it automatically",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "keeps the UI toggle in sync",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "No backend or framework required.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🌍 Optional: respect system preference by default",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "If no theme has been chosen yet, you can fall back to the user’s OS setting:",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "✨ Final result",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "You now have a modern theming system with:",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🎨 Three themes (light, dark, brand)",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🎚️ A polished segmented toggle switch",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "💾 Persistent user preferences",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "⚡ Instant UI updates via CSS variables",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "All in just a few lines of code.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "🚀 Final thoughts",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Dark mode is just the starting point.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "By combining CSS variables, a data attribute theme system, and a modern toggle switch, you can create a flexible theming architecture that grows with your product and gives users full control over their experience.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "And the best part? It’s simple, fast, and completely framework-free.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "",
            "type": "text"
          }
